He was a street worker, a graveyard gardener, and spent time in an Israeli kibbutz.
Green was born in 1946 to a Jewish working-class family in Bethnal Green, London.
He was a fan of blues musicians such as B.B. King and Muddy Waters.
At the age of eleven, he learned his first guitar.
At the age of 15, he began playing professional guitar and five years later he got the chance to play lead guitar for the instrumental band Peter B's Looners.
