In the midst of the blues boom, Green founded Fleetwood Mac in the summer of 1967, along with fellow Bluesbreakers Mick Fleetwood and John McVie.
The song "Albatross" composed by Green brought the group their first number one hit in the winter of 1968/69 and catapulted them to the top of the British music scene.
But the rapid rise soon showed its downsides: Green could not cope with the media hype, his experiments with the drug LSD became more and more extreme.
He later commented on the life between music and addiction in an interview: "The worst thing that happened to me in life is drugs - the best thing was to land a number one hit".
