Despite several minor solo successes, Green did not make a major comeback until 1996, when he rejoined a group of musicians he had befriended.
The British "Daily Telegraph" spoke of a rock star who had returned to Earth.
The group released several albums with the Peter Green Splinter Group until the band split up in 2004.
For music experts, he was already a blues legend during his lifetime - and with his soft sound one of the most influential guitarists of the past decades.
